# Notebook hygiene

## Header cell (mandatory first markdown cell)
```
# <notebook title>
**Purpose.** One sentence.
**Author / date.** <name> — <YYYY-MM-DD>.
**Inputs.** <data files>
**Outputs.** <figures, tables, panels — with paths under reports/>
**Plan section.** §X.Y of project_research_plan.md
**Confidence.** High / Medium / Low — with rationale.
```

## Path discipline
- Import paths from `config.paths`, never hardcode absolute paths.
  ```python
  from config.paths import DATA_DIR, REPORTS_DIR
  ```
- Never write outputs outside `reports/` from a notebook.

## Execution
- All notebooks must run top-to-bottom from a fresh kernel. CI may run `jupyter nbconvert --execute` on a random sample.
- `nbstripout` pre-commit hook strips outputs on commit. Do not disable.

## Checklist before committing
- [ ] Header cell present and filled.
- [ ] No `!pip install` cells.
- [ ] No `sys.path.insert` hacks.
- [ ] All hardcoded dates replaced by `config/events.yml` or `config/curation_snapshots.yml`.
- [ ] Final cell emits a `reports/run_summaries/` markdown entry.
